.TH "snd_usb_add_endpoint" 9 "snd_usb_add_endpoint" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_usb_add_endpoint \- Add an endpoint to an USB audio chip
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_usb_add_endpoint
.BI "(struct snd_usb_audio *chip "  ","
.BI "int ep_num "  ","
.BI "int type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
The chip
.IP "ep_num" 12
The number of the endpoint to use
.IP "type" 12
SND_USB_ENDPOINT_TYPE_DATA or SND_USB_ENDPOINT_TYPE_SYNC
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the requested endpoint has not been added to the given chip before,
a new instance is created.

Returns zero on success or a negative error code.

New endpoints will be added to chip->ep_list and freed by
calling \fBsnd_usb_endpoint_free_all\fP.

For SND_USB_ENDPOINT_TYPE_SYNC, the caller needs to guarantee that
bNumEndpoints > 1 beforehand.
